description: This person might be looking forward to that fight a little too much...

name: Driven
description: Big arch-rival vibes coming off of this one.

name: Nonchalant
description: Do they really not care? or is there perhaps another reason for their cold demeanor?

description: bye bye

name: Shiny Eyes
description: Like a perfectly polished marble.

name: Glossy Eyes
description: It's like the other one but a bit rounder, see?

name: Lustrous Eyes
description: Kawaii!

name: Gleaming Eyes
description: Have your eyes gleam with more light than the very sun gives off.

name: Bunned Up
description: Hair tied into a bun on the upper back of the head.

name: Asymmetrical Bob
description: Hair draped over one side of the head.

name: Faux Hawk
description: Hair combed forwards and up at the front.

name: Afro
description: Don't worry, it doesn't affect your hitbox.

name: French Bob
description: Girl next door vibes, except this one will hurl giant boulders at you if you step out of line.

name: Combed Sides
description: Hair on the sides of the head, neatly combed back.

name: Full on the Sides
description: Hair on the sides of the head, grown out a little to provide some precious extra volume.

name: Martialist's Headband
description: A stylish headband popular with fighters who strive towards self-improvement.

name: Defined Eyebrows
description: Looking good really is that simple.

name: Pencil Eyebrows
description: A single stroke of the brush is all you need.

name: Droplet Eyebrows
description: Like fresh morning dew, right on your forehead.

name: The Ringmaster
description: For when you REALLY want to put on a show.

name: The Inspector
description: Look at this distinguished gentleman!

name: Goatee
description: Bold move, but so worth it if you can pull it off.

name: Full Beard
description: Studies show that full beards can help prevent jaw injuries when impacted, beasides looking really cool.

name: V Neck Undershirt
description: A typical undershirt, but with a v neck. Cut not quite too low to be suitable for distraction tactics.

name: Martialist Dogi
description: A dogi-style undershirt, typical of fighters who follow the teachings of Jan-Kan.

name: All-Round Chestplate - Altered
description: One of the most popular patterns of chestplate amongst fighters, but with personalized and uniquely styled gambeson.

name: Poncho of the Devoted
description: An armor style most commonly associated with the Devoted, a group that views RUMBLE as sacred, a gift from above.

name: Martialist's Obi
description: A plain and simple belt neatly wrapped around the waist, indicative of the minimalistic ways of those who follow Jan-Kan.

name: Steadfast Belt
description: A style of belt typical of the weighty warriors who practice the way of oragoma, an old branch of RUMBLE where victory is achieved only via ring-out.

name: Challenger's Pauldron - Left
description: An armor pattern that was used in a now-forbidden branch of RUMBLE that would only end when 1 of the 2 fighters was killed by the other.

name: Challenger's Pauldron - Right
description: An armor pattern that was used in a now-forbidden branch of RUMBLE that would only end when 1 of the 2 fighters was killed by the other.

name: Challenger's Dual Pauldrons
description: An armor pattern that was used in a now-forbidden branch of RUMBLE. Dual Pauldrons were exclusive to warriors who had felled a remarkable amount of opponents.

name: Rolled Sleeves
description: Thick, long sleeves rolled up over the elbow. Often used for RUMBLE in colder climates, particularly by fighters from Arickteya.

name: All-Round Gauntlets - Altered
description: One of the most common types of gauntlet, decorated with an additional sleeve of cloth.

name: Bracers of the Devoted
description: Arm bracers commonly worn by Devoted. Only very few Devoted ever partake in RUMBLE, as it is reserved only for those of the upper echelon.

name: Martialist's Wristbands
description: Simple wristbands with sockets fit to hold Shiftstones, despite the fact that true martialists rarely ever make use of such items.

name: Joggers
description: Long, loose-fitted trousers popularized by Aricktayan fighters. Due to the high altitude of the land from which they hail, it is covered in snow almost all year round.

name: Short Shorts
description: While common in particularly hot climates, shortening the widely used shorts is often associated with rather fashion-conscious fighters. Just because you're about to get giant rocks lobbed at you is no reason not to look hella stylish.

name: Hakama
description: Each fold of the Hakama represents one of the virtues held in the highest regard by fighters who follow the way of Jan-Kan.

name: Shinguards of the Devoted
description: Shin protection in a style most associated with the Devoted. It lacks any proper footwear, as not to disrupt their connection to the earth.

name: Laminar Boots
description: An old style of boot that features many overlapping leather plates. It's said the origins of this design can be traced back to the east.
